1 § 3. TOWN MANAGER
2 (a) The Town Manager shall be the chief executive officer and the head of
3 the administrative branch of the Town government and shall be responsible to
4 the Selectboard for the efficient administration of the municipal affairs of the
5 Town.
6 (b) The Town Manager shall have the authority to hire, appoint, discipline,
7 and remove all Town employees, subject to the provisions of personnel rules
8 approved by the Selectboard. The Town Manager may authorize a department
9 head to hire, appoint, discipline, or remove an employee, subject to the
10 Manager’s discretion and supervision.
11 Sec. 4. EFFECTIVE DATE
12 This act shall take effect on passage.
